<p><b>Robert Maynard Pirsig</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1928-09-06"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="09-06"><a href="/wiki/September_6" title="September 6">September 6</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1928" title="1928">1928</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/Minneapolis,_Minnesota" title="Minneapolis, Minnesota" class="mw-redirect">Minneapolis, Minnesota</a>) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a> and <a href="/wiki/Philosopher" title="Philosopher" class="mw-redirect">philosopher</a>, mainly known as the <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a> of the book <i><a href="/wiki/Zen_and_the_Art_of_Motorcycle_Maintenance:_An_Inquiry_into_Values" title="Zen and the Art of Motorcycle Maintenance: An Inquiry into Values" class="mw-redirect">Zen and the Art of Motorcycle Maintenance: An Inquiry into Values</a></i> (1974), which has sold over four million copies around the world.</p>
